1. -- {Here are a few of the main theoretical chapters you should prioritize based on your rating and how often you are going to see the variations (ratings below are referring to online rapid rating):  A) If your rating is below 1200:  -London System (especially3.e3,3.dxc5,3.c3and3.Nf3?!which leads to blundering a piece many times!)  -2. Nf3 c5 Sidelines (especially3.dxc5and3.e3)  -3. Nf3 (not too far from3.d5in popularity)  -Benko Gambit Declined Fourth Move Sidelines (4.b3?!is very popular in this rating range which is good news for us!)  -Benko Gambit Fully Accepted 5...e6 (6.dxe6is the most popular in this rating range)  B) If your rating is between 1200-1600:  -London System (especially3.e3,3.c3and3.dxc5)  -2. Nf3 c5 Sidelines (especially3.dxc5,3.e3and3.c3)  -Benko Gambit Declined Fourth Move Sidelines (4.b3?!is still very popular in this rating range)  -Benko Gambit Half-Accepted 5. Nc3 Zaitsev (this picks up in popularity at this rating range but with almost everyone playing6.Nxb5instead of6.e4)  -Benko Gambit Fully Accepted 5...e6 (6.dxe6continues to be popular at this rating range)  C) If your rating is between 1600-2000:  -London System (mainly3.e3,3.c3and some3.d5)  -2. Nf3 c5 Sidelines (especially3.e3and3.c3)  -2. Nf3 c5 3. d5 b5 (this picks up in popularity at this rating range)  -Benko Gambit Half-Accepted 5. Nc3 Zaitsev (this continues to be relatively popular at this rating range with6.Nxb5still being most popular)  -Benko Gambit Fully Accepted 5...e6 (6.dxe6and6.Nc3are now seen the same amount of times)  D) If your rating is above 2000:  -London System (much less common now and if played, primarily with3.e3)  -2. Nf3 c5 3. d5 b5 (this continues to be relatively popular)  -Benko Gambit Half-Accepted 5. Nc3 Zaitsev 5. e3 Modern and 5. b6 (all three of these chapters are equally played)  -Benko Gambit Fully Accepted 5...e6 (6.Nc3now overtakes6.dxe6but not by a ton)} 
