10. Bg7 {We can afford to give up the c5-pawn.} 
11. Qxc5 {There have been a few games that have gone this way in the u2000 lichess database. However, fortunately for us this is a big blunder if you know the correct response.} 
11. Ne4 {We break the pin and counterattack white's queen and bishop.} 
12. Bxd8
12. Nxc5 {White cannot save both the bishop and b2-pawn. Once we capture on b2 we will also be trapping the rook on a1.} 
