 to capture it with the rook on a7 so that a future Nb5 move will gain a tempo on the rook. White scores about 62% from this position and the computers confirm that they are doing well here. With that being said, this variation and way of playing the opening is very interesting. However, it will not be the recommendation in this course.} 
6. Nc3 {The most common move. White defends their d5-pawn rather than trading on e6. If given the chance, White will play the move e4 next to further defend their d5-pawn. We cannot allow this!} 
6. exd5 {We trade on d5 immediately so that White cannot reinforce the pawn with e4.} 
7. Bg5 {If White doesn't capture the pawn back on d5 then we will keep it alive here.} 
7. d4
8. Bxf6 {White eliminates our knight and tries to pull our queen to f6 where it will be kicked around a bit.8.Nd5White decides to pile up on our pinned knight but we can break the pin with our bishop.8...Be79.Nxe7Qxe7⩱We've lost the bishop pair but have a big space advantage in the center and will capture ona6next with a strong position.8.Ne4This is similar to 8.Nd5 but even better for us since White doesn't get to win the bishop pair.8...Be79.Bxf6Bxf610.Nd6+Ke711.Nxc8+Qxc8∓White has gotten rid of our bishop pair but they had to trade off one of their bishops too. Our king is in the center but our space advantage and open queenside files give us a better position.} 
8. gxf6 {We avoid having our queen become a target and instead recapture with the g-pawn. This does weaken our pawn structure but we gain time here due to white's knight needing to move again and can follow-up with our own developing moves next.} 
9. Nd5 {9.Ne4?White centralizes their knight but doesn't block our d-pawn which allows us to gain more space now.9...d510.Nd2Bh6-+We have a huge mass of pawns in the center and now with the move ...Bh6 we make sure that White cannot attack our center with an e3-pawn break. White is suffocating here under their space disadvantage and we have a great position despite the pawn structure.} 
9. Nxa6 {We equalized material and have a big space advantage in the center. Next we will play ...Bb7 to harass white's knight and look to play ...Qa5+ in the future. Despite our pawn structure not being great, we still have a nice position with dynamic opportunities.} 
