9. Nxe4 {We happily oblige. White doesn't get enough of an attack in this variation to make up for giving the pawn back to us willingly.} 
10. Bc4 {White seeks to control the d5-square more. We need to start trading and eliminating white's active pieces.} 
10. Bxa6
11. Bxa6
11. Nxa6 {We want to play ...Nb4 next to challenge white's active d5-knight.} 
12. O-O
12. Nb4
13. Nxb4
13. cxb4 {We have a bit of a worse pawn structure, but the pawns are not weak. On the other hand, white's a2-pawn is a target with ...Ra5 followed by ...d5 and ...Qa8 being an idea we can work with.} 
