13. Qe8 {Once again, because the h7-pawn isn't attacked, then we don't need to trade bishop for knight yet.} 
14. Qf5
14. Bxg5 {Now that White was threatening h7 then we make the trade.} 
15. Bxg5
15. Ne5 {A novelty which gives Black a winning advantage immediately. The c4-bishop is under attack and ...d5 is a threat with a discovered attack on white's queen.} 
16. Bd5
16. d6
17. Qf4
17. h6
18. Bh4
18. Ng6
19. Qg3 {Threatening Qxg6 due to the pin on the f7-pawn.} 
19. Be6 {White's kingside pieces are completely frozen and Black will either capture the b2-pawn or land their queen on the e4-square with major threats soon.} 
20. b3
20. Bxd5
21. exd5
21. Qe4
22. f4
22. Qxd5 {Black is up a clean pawn and white's kingside pieces are still stuck in place.} 
