15. Qxd4 {Focusing on the center and giving up the rook on a8 in the process.} 
16. Qxa8
16. Qc4 {White is ahead the exchange but their king will have a hard time getting out of the center. We want to play ...Bb4 and ...Re8+ next.} 
17. Qb7 {White's only decent move. They need to get off the 8th rank so that ...Nc6 doesn't come with a tempo. White also wants to have the option of playing Qb5 later to offer a queen trade. Putting the queen on f3 wouldn't be as good since it would walk into ...Nd4 threats later too.} 
17. Bb4 {White has to deal with ...Bxc3+ and ...Re8+ ideas.} 
18. Be3 {The only move for White once again.} 
18. Nc6 {We threaten ...Rb8 gaining a tempo.} 
19. Qb5 {White absolutely must offer this queen trade.} 
19. Bxc3+
20. bxc3
20. Qxc3+
21. Ke2 {The only move for the rook on a1 to be defended.} 
21. Re8 {The fork on d4 is threatened now.} 
22. Rhd1
22. Nd4+
23. Rxd4
23. Qxd4 {Now that the smoke has settled, the position is balanced but I would still rather be Black. The rook on a1 is attacked, we can play ... Nd5 next to harass the bishop on e3 and threaten ...Nc3+ too and Rd1 doesn't work from White due to ...Qg4+ forking the king, rook and g2-pawn. White has some problems to solve here.} 
