6. Nxc5
7. Bg2
7. Qb6 {We can take advantage of white's lack of development by attacking the b2-pawn quickly. Playing ...Nce4 is also an idea too.} 
8. Qc2 {It looks like this defends against both of our ideas.} 
8. Nce4 {But we can play ...Nce4 anyways! The queen is needed on the c2-square to defend the b2-pawn and trapped rook on a1.} 
9. e3
9. Qb4+ {White will now have to make a concession in their position. Do they lose a pawn, forfeit the ability to castle or end up with a bad pawn structure?} 
10. Nd2
10. Nxd2
11. Qxd2
11. Qxc4 {We're ahead a clean pawn.} 
