2. c5 {Throughout the main chapters of the course we have focused on the third moves being3.d5(which we respond to with3...b5entering the Benko Gambit) and3.Nf3(which we respond to with3...cxd4). In this chapter we will be looking at all of the third move sidelines that are not3.d5or3.Nf3.  The good news for us is that all of the sidelines are very non-critical and will give us no problems at all. In most of these situations we should actually be able to get some kind of advantage for ourselves which will be pleasant.} 
