11. Qb3 {This seems reasonable for White because they attack our knight and b7-pawn at the same time. There is a bit of a problem as we will see though.} 
11. Be6 {We can trade off our b7-pawn for white's d4-pawn and get a very active position and chase around white's queen.} 
12. Qxb7
12. Nxd4
13. Nxd4
13. Bxd4
14. Nxd5
14. Bxd5
15. Qa6
15. e6 {We are better here due to our more active bishops and pressure against both sides of the board (b2-pawn and f2/g2-pawns). Playing ...Qf6 or ...Qh4 are some of our immediate ideas.} 
