15. fxg6
15. fxg6 {And here we recapture in a non-standard way that is the strongest response. Usually recaptures on g6 are done using the h-pawn since you are 'capturing towards the center' but by using the f-pawn we open up our rook. Despite being down a pawn, we have good compensation with our terrific piece activity and good attacking chances on the kingside. White's pieces are stuck on the queenside and will take a long time to manevuer towards the kingside to keep their king safe.} 
