3. e3 {White reinforces their d4-pawn but blocks in their c1-bishop and doesn't fight for the center immediately. For this reason, we should go ahead and take the center.} 
3. d5 {Gaining a space advantage as Black in most openings should be difficult to accomplish if White is playing ambitiously but if our opponent is playing passively then we should be taking the center ourselves.} 
4. b3 {White goes for the Colle-Zukertort set-up which is similar to the regular Colle system but the main difference is the bishop going to b2 and not being blocked in by a pawn on c3. The main drawback to this is revealed with our next move though.} 
4. cxd4 {By immediately trading pawns on d4 we are enticing White to recapture with their e3-pawn which will then be in the way of the bishop on b2. If we had not made this trade then White would have been able to play dxc5 later on and the bishop on b2 would have been opened up and active.} 
5. Nxd4 {If White recaptures with the knight then they have less control of the center.} 
5. e5 {We kick the knight out of the center and gain a bigger space advantage.} 
