6. Bxf2+ {Instead of taking the b2-pawn immediately, we go after the f2-pawn first! We play this in order to divert white's queen after from defending the knight on c3 so that capturing the b2-pawn will result in a fork on the rook and undefended knight.} 
7. Qxf2
7. Qxb2 {White either loses the rook or knight with check and will be down material.} 
