15. h4
15. Ng3 {Once White plays h4 then they open up the g3-square for us to use to maneuver towards f5 with tempo.} 
16. Rg1
16. Ngf5 {Black has a very nice position. The knight on f5 is placed extremely well. Next we may play ... h5 to lock up the kingside then continue to focus on the queenside along with white's weak h4 and f4 pawns. Castling either direction is possible from here and if the knight on c3 ever moves then I would consider playing ...Bb5 to trade off the light-square bishops.} 
