5. f4 {White's most popular choice in this move order. They are able to use the fact that the knight isn't developed to f3 yet and is not blocking the f-pawn in order to push it to f4 first. This does give White increased control of the e5-square and makes it difficult for us to play this . ..e5 pawn break ourselves but now White is stuck with the weak e4-square in the long-term.} 
