11. Rad8 {We develop the rook and get ready to play ...Ne4 soon.} 
12. Ndf3 {White moves their knight away from controlling the e4-square. Because of this, we can shift our plan from playing ...Ne8 and ...f6 to playing ...Ne4 and ...f6 instead.} 
12. Nxe5
13. fxe5
13. Ne4 {We cement our control of the e4-square and next we will play ...f6 to break apart white's e5-pawn and open the f-file. We have a good position here, especially in part due to white's c1-bishop being very passive.} 
