 {In this chapter, you will see 23 different model games that start with opening variations shown throughout the theoretical chapters of the course.   These games come from a wide variety of time controls and player levels. Some of the games are played between strong and weak players (with hundreds of rating point differences) to show you how to play the optimal plans when the opponent is not offering the toughest resistance. Some of the games are played between two equally strong players, where resistance is shown, but we also see how to overcome it.   We'll see games played by super-Grandmasters such as Magnus Carlsen, Daniil Dubov, Leinier Dominguez, and Jeffery Xiong. I've also included a few of my own over-the-board tournament games. In addition to over-the-board games, we will also see some rapid or blitz games in this chapter.   Despite these particular games not being played at the same high level as classical over-the-board games, the IMs and GMs playing these games will still demonstrate a very high level of play that we can learn from, despite the reduced time control.   Within each game, I have also included a link where you can reference the variation in the theoretical chapter that explains the opening moves in more detail. Enjoy!} 1. --
